  "rationale": "<p>Choice B is correct. Among the 12 brown-coated puppies, 4 have hazel eyes. Therefore the fraction with hazel eyes is 4/12 (which simplifies to 1/3). Choice A is incorrect because 4/40 uses all 40 puppies as the denominator instead of conditioning on brown-coated puppies. Choice C is incorrect because 4/14 is the fraction of all hazel-eyed puppies that are brown-coated. Choice D is incorrect because 12/40 is the fraction of all puppies that are brown-coated.</p>",
